{{Infobox French commune |name = Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre |commune status = [[Communes of France|Commune]] |image = Église Notre-Dame de Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre (2).JPG |caption = The church of Notre-Dame |arrondissement = Avranches |canton = Villedieu-les-Poêles-Rouffigny |INSEE = 50144 |postal code = 50670 |mayor = Daniel Tourgis |term = 2020&ndash;2026 |intercommunality = Villedieu Intercom |coordinates = {{coord|48.7875|-1.1078|format=dms|display=inline,title}} |elevation m = 264 |elevation min m = 130 |elevation max m = 315 |area km2 = 17.25 |population = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_total}} |population date = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_as_of}} |population footnotes = {{France metadata Wikidata|population_footnotes}} }} '''Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre''' ({{IPA-fr|kuluvʁɛ bwabənatʁ}}) is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Manche]] [[Departments of France|department]] in [[Normandy (administrative region)|Normandy]] in north-western [[France]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.map-france.com/Coulouvray-Boisbenatre-50670/|title = COULOUVRAY-BOISBENATRE - Map of Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre 50670 France}}</ref>
==Geography== ===Climate=== Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre has a [[oceanic climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification]] ''Cfb''). The average annual temperature in Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre is {{cvt|10.4|C}}. The average annual rainfall is {{cvt|1378.3|mm}} with December as the wettest month. The temperatures are highest on average in August, at around {{cvt|17.1|C}}, and lowest in January, at around {{convert|4.3|C}}. The highest temperature ever recorded in Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre was {{cvt|36.5|C}} on 5 August 2003; the coldest temperature ever recorded was {{cvt|-13.5|C}} on 7 February 1991. {{Weather box |location= Coulouvray-Boisbenâtre (1981–2010 averages, extremes 1988−present) |metric first= Y |single line= Y |Jan record high C = 14.5 |Feb record high C = 20.5 |Mar record high C = 23.0 |Apr record high C = 27.0 |May record high C = 28.5 |Jun record high C = 34.5 |Jul record high C = 36.0 |Aug record high C = 36.5 |Sep record high C = 32.1 |Oct record high C = 27.5 |Nov record high C = 21.0 |Dec record high C = 14.0 |year record high C = 36.5 |Jan high C = 6.6 |Feb high C = 7.9 |Mar high C = 10.6 |Apr high C = 12.9 |May high C = 16.9 |Jun high C = 19.7 |Jul high C = 21.4 |Aug high C = 21.7 |Sep high C = 18.8 |Oct high C = 14.7 |Nov high C = 10.0 |Dec high C = 6.8 |year high C = 14.0 |Jan mean C = 4.3 |Feb mean C = 4.9 |Mar mean C = 7.1 |Apr mean C = 8.8 |May mean C = 12.5 |Jun mean C = 15.0 |Jul mean C = 16.9 |Aug mean C = 17.1 |Sep mean C = 14.6 |Oct mean C = 11.4 |Nov mean C = 7.2 |Dec mean C = 4.4 |year mean C = 10.4 |Jan low C = 1.9 |Feb low C = 2.0 |Mar low C = 3.7 |Apr low C = 4.7 |May low C = 8.1 |Jun low C = 10.4 |Jul low C = 12.4 |Aug low C = 12.5 |Sep low C = 10.4 |Oct low C = 8.1 |Nov low C = 4.5 |Dec low C = 2.0 |year low C = 6.8 |Jan record low C = -13.5 |Feb record low C = -13.5 |Mar record low C = -8.0 |Apr record low C = -5.0 |May record low C = -1.0 |Jun record low C = 2.5 |Jul record low C = 5.5 |Aug record low C = 4.5 |Sep record low C = 3.0 |Oct reco