'''Crollon''' ({{IPA-fr|kʁɔlɔ̃}}) is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Manche]] [[Departments of France|department]] in [[Normandy (administrative region)|Normandy]] in north-western [[France]]. It had 283 inhabitants as of 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insee.fr/fr/statistiques/1405599?geo=COM-50155|title=Comparateur de territoires−Commune de Crollon (50155) {{!}} Insee|website=www.insee.fr|language=fr|access-date=2017-09-18}}</ref> Historically, Crollon has ranged in size from a maximum of 500 inhabitants in 1821 to a minimum of 183 in 1982.<ref>{{Cassini-Ehess|11184|Crollon}}</ref> Christian Pacilly became mayor of Crollon in 2008, replacing Arsène Bouteloup, who had been mayor for the previous 32 years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ouest-france.fr/arsene-bouteloup-passera-la-main-en-mars-prochain-28339|title=Arsène Bouteloup passera la main en mars prochain|work=Ouest-France.fr|access-date=2017-09-18|language=fr-FR}}</ref>

