|demonym                = Donvillais
|website                = [http://www.ville-donville-les-bains.fr www.ville-donville-les-bains.fr]
}}
'''Donville-les-Bains''' ({{IPA-fr|dɔ̃vil le bɛ̃}}) is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Manche]] [[Departments of France|department]], northwestern [[France]].

==Introduction==
Donville-les-Bains is located just outside Granville, a port on the Norman coast noted for ferry traffic to the Channel Islands. Rail service is available from Granville to Paris on a regular basis provided by SNCF, the French National Railway.

The town is also the origin of the English language surname Dunville/Dumville (originally Donville),{{cn|date=January 2017}} which is found throughout the UK and former British colonies.{{cn|date=January 2017}} People descended from this Norman line can be found in concentrations around Toronto, Thunder Bay, Chicago, Detroit, St. Louis, and South Carolina.{{cn|date=January 2017}} (However, Dunville, Newfoundland was not named after Donville-les-Bains; Dunville was named after the founding Dunphy family.)

==Heraldry==
{{Blazon-arms
| img1=Blason Donville-les-Bains.svg|
| legend1=Arms of Donville-les-Bains
| text=<small>The arms of Donville-les-Bains are [[blazon]]ed :<br />''Gules, a sea-horse [i.e. a mythical [[Hippocampus (mythology)|hippocampus]]], and in chief a sun of 8 points Or.''</small>
}}

