{{Infobox musical artist | name = Stick Against Stone | image = | alias = SAS, [[Pancreatic Ballet]], [[Stick Against Stone Orchestra]] | origin = [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]], United States | genre = [[Post-punk]], [[no wave]], [[dub music|dub]], [[funk]], [[free jazz]], [[Art punk]], [[worldbeat]] | years_active = 1981–1990 - 2011- | label = [[MediaGroove]], T.M.I. | associated_acts = Carsickness, Medicine, [[Mental Block Party]], [[The Invertebrates]], Body Rhythm, No Shelter, The Dark, Decline, The Little Wretches | website = [http://www.stickagainststone.com/ Official website] | current_members = Sari Jozokos Morninghawk, Bob Wenzel, Andrew McAuley, Tom Shad, Jesse Kranzler, Kaori Kiki Nakajima | past_members = Brook Duer, Richard Vitale, Jim Laugelli, John H. Creighton Jr.,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/4578845-John-Creighton|title=John Creighton|website=[[Discogs]]}}</ref> Chuck Sullivan, Geraldine Murray, David Soule, Anne Galhagher, Lyn Thomas (Freeman), Herman Pearl, Kevin Amos, Daniel Ramirez, Robert “Xeres” Shepard, David Mihaly, J.B. }}
'''Stick Against Stone''' is a [[Post-punk]] / [[No wave|No Wave]] band from [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]]; that later resided in [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]]; [[Eugene, Oregon]] and [[San Francisco]], [[California]] and remained active (in no less than six incarnations) between 1981 and 1990. The group returned to performing in 2011 and currently resides in the [[New York City]] area.
Since their founding, the band went through several line-up changes, but never released a full album until 2010 – and it wasn't until the 2014 release of ''[http://stickagainststone.com/catalog/oregon-bootleg-tapes-live/ The Oregon Bootleg Tapes - Live]'' (a live recording from 1985) that critical attention finally arrived in the form of positive reviews in [[New York (magazine)|New York Magazine]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = The To Do List|url = http://nymag.com/nymag/culture/to-do/to-do-2014-7-14/index1.html|website = NYMag.com|publisher=New York Magazine|access-date=2016-02-07}}</ref> [[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = First Listen: "Instant" From Stick Against Stone's The Oregon Bootleg Tapes|url = http://www.vibe.com/2014/05/first-listen-stick-against-stone-oregon-bootleg-tapes/|website = Vibe|date = 16 May 2014|access-date = 2016-02-07}}</ref> [[Wax Poetics]],<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.waxpoetics.com/wax-poetics-magazine/wax-poetics-issue-60-blondie-bw-sza/|title = Wax Poetics #60|date = |access-date = 2020-01-16|website = |publisher = |last = Gale|first = Ezra}}</ref> [[Cuepoint]]<ref>{{Cite web|title = Robert Christgau:Expert Witness: Baseball Project / Hamell on Trial / Richmond Fontaine / Delines /Stick Against Stone /Ry Cooder /Modern Baseball, (Yep Roc), (New West), (El Cortez '02)|url = https://medium.com/cuepoint/robert-christgau-expert-witness-25b726055213#.cvmhzgtkm|website = Medium|date = 2014-10-24|access-date = 2016-02-07|first = Robert|last = Christgau}}</ref> ([[Robert Christgau]]) and [[Pitchfork Media|Pitchfork]],<ref name=":0" /> where writer Miles Raymer remarked about the group: ''“They had their eyes on the 'there and then', but they were playing 20 years into the future.”''<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title = Stick Against Stone: The Oregon Bootleg Tapes|url = http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/19364-stick-against-stone-the-oregon-bootleg-tapes/|website = Pitchfork|access-date = 2016-02-07|language = en-US}}</ref>
