{{Short description|Canadian actor}} {{Infobox person | name = Mark Humphrey | image = | caption = | birthname = Mark Adrian Humphrey | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1960|12|27}} | birth_place = [[Vancouver|Vancouver, British Columbia]], Canada | death_date = | death_place = | othername = | occupation = Actor | years_active = 1985–present | spouse = | website = http://www.markhumphrey.com/ | nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]] }} '''Mark Adrian Humphrey''' (born December 27, 1960) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[actor]] best known for the role of Jake Antonelli in the Canadian television series ''[[E.N.G.]]''<ref name="E.N.G.">{{cite news|title=''E.N.G.'' Canadian Drama,|url=http://www.museum.tv/eotv/eng.htm|accessdate= 18 October 2014|newspaper=Museum.tv}}</ref><ref name="E.N.G. Photo">{{cite news|title=''E.N.G.'' Cast Photo,|url=http://www.broadcasting-history.ca/ccf_resources/ccf_resources-programming/television/ccf_programming_pictures/70_lrg.jpg|accessdate=1 October 2014|newspaper=Broadcasting-History.ca|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923194658/http://www.broadcasting-history.ca/ccf_resources/ccf_resources-programming/television/ccf_programming_pictures/70_lrg.jpg|archivedate=23 September 2015}}</ref> In 1988 he made his feature film debut in the film ''[[Iron Eagle II]]'' <ref>{{cite magazine |title=''Iron Eagle II'' Review |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=December 31, 1987|url=https://www.variety.com/review/VE1117792030.html?categoryid=31&cs=1 |accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="Iron Eagle II">{{cite news|title=''Iron Eagle II'',|url=http://www.moviestillsdb.com/movies/iron-eagle-ii-i95382/dd66921d|accessdate= 18 October 2014|newspaper=MovieStillDB.com}}</ref> as Captain Matt Cooper, Doug Masters' ([[Jason Gedrick]]) surviving best friend. Humphrey has been featured in other films and in several television movies. In 2005 he starred in ''Living With the Enemy'' with [[Sarah Lancaster]]. In 2006 he starred in ''[[The Wives He Forgot]]'' with [[Molly Ringwald]] as a handsome amnesiac. In 2007 he appeared in ''[[Still Small Voices]]'' with [[Catherine Bell (actress)|Catherine Bell]]. Humphrey has also appeared in numerous television series.
==Life and career== Humphrey was born in [[Vancouver|Vancouver, British Columbia]], to Sidney and [[Jack Humphrey (producer)|Jack Humphrey]]. His family relocated to [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]] in 1967, where his father worked as a producer for [[CBC Radio]] and [[CBC Television|Television]]. After graduating from high school, Humphrey moved to New York City to study acting at the [[Lee Strasberg Theatre and Film Institute]]. Humphrey spent five years in New York, later returning to Toronto, and eventually relocating to California.
Humphrey has four siblings. His three brothers, [[John Humphrey (bass player)|John]], [[Paul Humphrey (singer/songwriter)|Paul]], and Andy, are professional musicians. His sister, Lesley, is a former [[Ford Models|Ford model]].
In 2009 Humphrey appeared in the Canadian dramatic series ''[[Paradise Falls]]'',<ref name="Paradise Falls">{{cite news|last=Wild|first=Diane|title=''Paradise Falls Season 3'', |date=August 9, 2007|url=http://www.tv-eh.com/2007/08/09/paradise-falls-season-three/|accessdate= 1 October 2014|publisher=TV-Eh.com}}</ref> and the television movies ''Encounter with Danger'' with [[Shannen Doherty]], and ''[[Hostile Makeover]]'' with [[Maggie Lawson]]. He appeared in the 2010 feature film ''Summer Eleven''. In 2015 Humphrey joined the cast of the [[Hallmark Channel]] series ''[[When Calls the Heart]]'' as mysterious preacher Frank Hogan.<ref name="When Calls the Heart">{{cite magazine|last=Wang|first=K.L. Connie|title=''Mark Humphrey: When Calls the Heart's Newest Blessing'', |date=June 9, 2015|url=http://parade.com/403893/klconniewang/mark-humphrey-when-calls-the-hearts-newest-blessing/|accessdate= 13 June 2015|magazine=[[Parade (magazine)|Parade Magazine]]}}</ref><ref name="When Calls the Heart Interview">{{cite news|title=''Interview With Actor Mark Humphrey, "When Calls the Heart"'', |date=February 17, 2017|url=http://mydevotionalthoughts.net/2017/02/interview-with-actor-mark-humphrey-when-calls-the-heart.html|accessdate= 25 April 2017|publisher=[[My Devotional Thoughts]]}}</ref>
Humphrey appeared in the 2005 independent film ''[[Cruel But Necessary]]'' with his ex-wife [[Wendel Meldrum]] and their son [[Luke Humphrey]].<ref name="Canada.com">{{cite news|last=Schaefer |first=Glen |title=''Small Project Fed Director's Soul'', |date=September 2007 |url=http://www.canada.com/cityguides/vancouver/story.html?id=a3c8df11-b2c1-4f49-8cfd-1294e932ff76&k=68051 |newspaper=[[The Province|The Vancouver Province]] |accessdate=1 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017003117/http://www.canada.com/cityguides/vancouver/story.html?id=a3c8df11-b2c1-4f49-8cfd-1294e932ff76&k=68051 |archivedate=17 October 2014 }}</ref>
